{%- comment -%}
  Rendered once inside <head> of layout/theme.liquid (and password.liquid).

  Currently emits merchant-pasted Custom CSS so it can override anything
  in panthor-dev.css / components.css without touching the original files.

  If you later want merchant-controlled brand colors / font scale / layout
  toggles, add :root { --var: {{ settings.X }}; } blocks here and the
  matching settings to config/settings_schema.json. Keep the
  `{% if settings.X != blank %}` guard so empty settings never override
  the design's defaults (this is what bit us with the dark-mode bug).
{%- endcomment -%}
{%- if settings.custom_css != blank -%}
<style id="theme-custom-css">
{{ settings.custom_css }}
</style>
{%- endif -%}
